SIMPLE: intimidate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intimidate
<hw>In*tim"i*date</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Intimidated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Intimidating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[LL.
<ets>intimidatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>intimidare</ets> to frighten;
pref. <ets>in-</ets> in + <ets>timidus</ets> fearful, timid: cf. F.
<ets>intimider</ets>. See <er>Timid</er>.]</ety> <def>To make timid or
fearful; to inspire of affect with fear; to deter, as by threats; to
dishearten; to abash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Now guilt, once harbored in the conscious breast,⟦br⟧
<qex>Intimidates</qex> the brave, degrades the great.</q>
<rj><qau>Johnson.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To dishearten; dispirit; abash; deter; frighten;
terrify; daunt; cow.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>intimidated</ent>⟦br⟧
